-- Apple iPod Nano Music Player May Pose Fire Hazard, Trade Ministry Says
-- Adam Le
-- 2010-07-29T04:42:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-29/apple-ipod-nano-music-player-may-pose-fire-hazard-trade-ministry-says.html

          
          
             Japan’s trade ministry asked
 Apple Inc.  to report by Aug. 4 on measures the company will
take to prevent a fire hazard the ministry said is related to
the iPod Nano portable music player.  
 Six incidents involving the 2005 model Nano catching
fire while being charged have been reported to the ministry
since 2008,  Ministry of Economy, Trade and Industry  spokesman
Hiroshi Miyashita said today by telephone. There were an
additional 21 cases involving incidents where the players
overheated and emitted smoke since 2005, he said.  
 Jill Tan , a spokeswoman for Apple Asia in Hong Kong said
she didn’t know about the incidents or ministry’s request.
The ministry made the request in a statement dated yesterday.  
